	<!-- Introduction -->
	<!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
	<purpose>
		<p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies the application module for the representation of a location at which a product or resource item may be situated. It provides a capability to represent a location in terms of geographic position, an organizational based coding, a postal address or a product based coding, such as a zone within a product. It does not describe location within product geometry.</p>
	</purpose>
	<!-- Items in scope -->
	<inscope>
		<li>the geographic position  of products, resource items or activitties; <example>A product may be located by latitude, longitude, and altitude or depth.</example>
		</li>
		<li>the specification of location by use of organizational based codes;</li>
		<li>the specification of location by postal address, including nested addresses;</li>
		<li>the specification of location by product based codes, or zone within a product, including nested locations;</li>
		<li>the  location relative to another location.</li>
	</inscope>
	<!-- Items out of scope -->
	<outscope>
		<li>the definition of product geometry;</li>
		<li>the location of an attachment slot.</li>
	</outscope>
